WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.950 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.950 --> 00:00:07.920 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:07.920 --> 00:00:28.150 align:middle line:90%


00:00:28.150 --> 00:00:29.900 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA MEREDITH: I
think that most of us

00:00:29.900 --> 00:00:32.810 align:middle line:10%
experience a sense of
renewal, even magic,

00:00:32.810 --> 00:00:35.680 align:middle line:10%
during the time we spend in
nature or in our gardens.

00:00:35.680 --> 00:00:37.425 align:middle line:84%
In ancient times, it
was well understood

00:00:37.425 --> 00:00:40.370 align:middle line:84%
that the outdoors belong
to a kingdom of beings

00:00:40.370 --> 00:00:43.970 align:middle line:84%
who were responsible for its
life force, the Devic Kingdom.

00:00:43.970 --> 00:00:46.870 align:middle line:84%
Elves, fairies, brownies,
gnomes, undines,

00:00:46.870 --> 00:00:48.790 align:middle line:84%
and many other
invisible creatures

00:00:48.790 --> 00:00:52.030 align:middle line:84%
are tasked with keeping
nature alive with wonder.

00:00:52.030 --> 00:00:54.140 align:middle line:84%
Linda Cooper began
tapping into this kingdom

00:00:54.140 --> 00:00:56.390 align:middle line:84%
many years ago as a
landscape designer,

00:00:56.390 --> 00:00:59.810 align:middle line:84%
and has been asking them about
their world for as many years.

00:00:59.810 --> 00:01:02.590 align:middle line:84%
She's with us today to take
us on a magical mystery

00:01:02.590 --> 00:01:05.750 align:middle line:84%
tour of the unseen
world surrounding us.

00:01:05.750 --> 00:01:07.240 align:middle line:90%
I'm so happy to have you here.

00:01:07.240 --> 00:01:11.310 align:middle line:84%
And what a sweet, just
a sweet and magical book

00:01:11.310 --> 00:01:12.470 align:middle line:90%
you've written.

00:01:12.470 --> 00:01:13.140 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDA SHAYLOR COOPER:
Thank you, Regina.

00:01:13.140 --> 00:01:14.630 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I just, I love it.

00:01:14.630 --> 00:01:17.620 align:middle line:84%
And when I was-- I've talked
to you quite a bit off camera

00:01:17.620 --> 00:01:18.930 align:middle line:90%
about all of this.

00:01:18.930 --> 00:01:20.890 align:middle line:84%
And we need to go
back a little bit.

00:01:20.890 --> 00:01:22.720 align:middle line:84%
Go back to the beginning
of where you first

00:01:22.720 --> 00:01:24.600 align:middle line:84%
started connecting
with this world,

00:01:24.600 --> 00:01:29.860 align:middle line:84%
and then the deal you had to
broker to make this book come

00:01:29.860 --> 00:01:31.830 align:middle line:90%
about, which is fascinating.

00:01:31.830 --> 00:01:35.240 align:middle line:10%
>>COOPER:Yes, well, I've been
interested in the fairy realm

00:01:35.240 --> 00:01:36.850 align:middle line:10%
ever since I was a little girl.

00:01:36.850 --> 00:01:39.280 align:middle line:10%
I was born in
South Africa, and I

00:01:39.280 --> 00:01:41.740 align:middle line:10%
used to go hide under
the bushes and feel

00:01:41.740 --> 00:01:44.030 align:middle line:10%
like I was in fairyland.

00:01:44.030 --> 00:01:47.360 align:middle line:10%
Then when I grew up, I
kind of forgot about it.

00:01:47.360 --> 00:01:50.220 align:middle line:84%
And I was looking for
my passion in life,

00:01:50.220 --> 00:01:54.870 align:middle line:84%
and I ended up being passionate
about being in my own garden.

00:01:54.870 --> 00:01:58.370 align:middle line:84%
I became so enamored
with the plants

00:01:58.370 --> 00:02:01.190 align:middle line:84%
and how they combined
and all of that,

00:02:01.190 --> 00:02:06.700 align:middle line:84%
that I ended up waking up
to the fairy realm again.

00:02:06.700 --> 00:02:07.825 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, as an adult.

00:02:07.825 --> 00:02:08.130 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:02:08.130 --> 00:02:08.949 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: Exactly.

00:02:08.949 --> 00:02:10.344 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:02:10.344 --> 00:02:12.260 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA:And you had a
unique experience, too,

00:02:12.260 --> 00:02:13.720 align:middle line:90%
when you were a young woman.

00:02:13.720 --> 00:02:17.430 align:middle line:84%
Where most of us are like, just
pounding away on our careers

00:02:17.430 --> 00:02:20.960 align:middle line:84%
or child-bearing
and rearing, you

00:02:20.960 --> 00:02:22.310 align:middle line:90%
took a break with your husband.

00:02:22.310 --> 00:02:24.480 align:middle line:84%
I thought that was so
fascinating what you ended up

00:02:24.480 --> 00:02:24.990 align:middle line:90%
doing.

00:02:24.990 --> 00:02:25.906 align:middle line:90%
Let's talk about that.

00:02:25.906 --> 00:02:27.600 align:middle line:84%
Because it gave you
the space most of us

00:02:27.600 --> 00:02:28.917 align:middle line:90%
don't have the courage to take.

00:02:28.917 --> 00:02:29.500 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: Yes.

00:02:29.500 --> 00:02:30.900 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: To get in
touch with all of this.

00:02:30.900 --> 00:02:32.600 align:middle line:84%
And tell us about
your grand adventure.

00:02:32.600 --> 00:02:33.100 align:middle line:90%
I love this.

00:02:33.100 --> 00:02:36.220 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: Oh, it was amazing.

00:02:36.220 --> 00:02:39.370 align:middle line:84%
At around 25 years old,
I married this lovely man

00:02:39.370 --> 00:02:43.410 align:middle line:84%
who happened to be a
lawyer, attorney type.

00:02:43.410 --> 00:02:45.440 align:middle line:84%
And after seven
years of marriage,

00:02:45.440 --> 00:02:46.830 align:middle line:90%
he was so stressed out.

00:02:46.830 --> 00:02:49.680 align:middle line:84%
I mean, most the time,
I was in la la land,

00:02:49.680 --> 00:02:51.650 align:middle line:90%
but he was in the courtroom.

00:02:51.650 --> 00:02:54.970 align:middle line:84%
And I just was like,
this is not fun.

00:02:54.970 --> 00:02:58.690 align:middle line:84%
Because it was like living
on the razor's edge for him.

00:02:58.690 --> 00:03:02.300 align:middle line:84%
So I got to a place where I
said, Cooper I'm out here.

00:03:02.300 --> 00:03:04.830 align:middle line:84%
And he's like, no,
don't leave me.

00:03:04.830 --> 00:03:06.570 align:middle line:84%
So I said well,
let's go traveling.

00:03:06.570 --> 00:03:09.270 align:middle line:84%
Because I had done a lot
of traveling in my life.

00:03:09.270 --> 00:03:14.990 align:middle line:84%
So he, being the first Eagle
Scout in Orange County,

00:03:14.990 --> 00:03:17.910 align:middle line:84%
knew how to do
everything camping-wise.

00:03:17.910 --> 00:03:20.670 align:middle line:90%
I have never been a camper.

00:03:20.670 --> 00:03:22.570 align:middle line:90%
Anyway, it took us about a year.

00:03:22.570 --> 00:03:26.020 align:middle line:84%
We decided to get
in a Volkswagen bus

00:03:26.020 --> 00:03:30.420 align:middle line:84%
that we both outfitted, and
go to the tip of South America

00:03:30.420 --> 00:03:31.669 align:middle line:90%
and come back in one year.

00:03:31.669 --> 00:03:32.710 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's so cool.

00:03:32.710 --> 00:03:33.500 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: It was amazing.

00:03:33.500 --> 00:03:33.970 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's a dream.

00:03:33.970 --> 00:03:35.595 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: And we were
in our early 30s.

00:03:35.595 --> 00:03:37.790 align:middle line:84%
And friends of ours who
were around the same age

00:03:37.790 --> 00:03:39.220 align:middle line:90%
thought we were just nuts.

00:03:39.220 --> 00:03:42.380 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Especially him
leaving his legal practice.

00:03:42.380 --> 00:03:42.880 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:03:42.880 --> 00:03:43.175 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: Exactly.

00:03:43.175 --> 00:03:43.675 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:03:43.675 --> 00:03:48.660 align:middle line:84%
But it gave us the
opportunity of being retired

00:03:48.660 --> 00:03:51.676 align:middle line:84%
at the age in our early
30s, which was amazing.

00:03:51.676 --> 00:03:53.050 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: To have
all that energy

00:03:53.050 --> 00:03:53.965 align:middle line:90%
and curiosity and adventure.

00:03:53.965 --> 00:03:54.250 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: Yeah.

00:03:54.250 --> 00:03:55.560 align:middle line:84%
At first, we didn't
know what to do with it,

00:03:55.560 --> 00:03:58.030 align:middle line:84%
except just figure out where
we were going every day

00:03:58.030 --> 00:03:59.670 align:middle line:90%
and where to get food.

00:03:59.670 --> 00:04:01.530 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, I almost had
a nervous breakdown

00:04:01.530 --> 00:04:04.670 align:middle line:90%
crossing the border in Tijuana.

00:04:04.670 --> 00:04:08.100 align:middle line:84%
I was going into a
third-world country.

00:04:08.100 --> 00:04:10.850 align:middle line:90%
Anyway, we survived it.

00:04:10.850 --> 00:04:13.370 align:middle line:84%
It took him four
months to relax.

00:04:13.370 --> 00:04:14.990 align:middle line:90%
And that was amazing.

00:04:14.990 --> 00:04:20.149 align:middle line:84%
But where it supported
me in this work

00:04:20.149 --> 00:04:25.120 align:middle line:84%
that I have eventually come to
honor and be passionate about,

00:04:25.120 --> 00:04:27.180 align:middle line:84%
was because we were
in so much nature.

00:04:27.180 --> 00:04:29.410 align:middle line:90%
We'd stay out in the wilderness.

00:04:29.410 --> 00:04:31.340 align:middle line:90%
We'd stay in national parks.

00:04:31.340 --> 00:04:37.350 align:middle line:84%
I was imprinted with the
way Mother Earth designs

00:04:37.350 --> 00:04:39.080 align:middle line:90%
her gardens.

00:04:39.080 --> 00:04:43.040 align:middle line:84%
So when I became a garden
fairy, when we got back,

00:04:43.040 --> 00:04:46.050 align:middle line:84%
we actually went
traveling for a year.

00:04:46.050 --> 00:04:49.132 align:middle line:84%
And then we got a bigger
vehicle because he wanted to go.

00:04:49.132 --> 00:04:50.590 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: A school
bus as I recall.

00:04:50.590 --> 00:04:53.610 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: A school
bus that he outfitted.

00:04:53.610 --> 00:04:55.820 align:middle line:84%
I said, I am not living
with you in a Volkswagen

00:04:55.820 --> 00:04:56.990 align:middle line:90%
bus for another year.

00:04:56.990 --> 00:04:57.890 align:middle line:90%
I'm sorry.

00:04:57.890 --> 00:04:59.570 align:middle line:90%
So we end up with a school bus.

00:04:59.570 --> 00:05:03.610 align:middle line:90%
And we outfitted it into an RV.

00:05:03.610 --> 00:05:04.770 align:middle line:90%
And he did all the work.

00:05:04.770 --> 00:05:05.950 align:middle line:90%
We both did, actually.

00:05:05.950 --> 00:05:07.910 align:middle line:90%
But he figured it out.

00:05:07.910 --> 00:05:11.160 align:middle line:84%
And we had a 2 and
1/2 year difference,

00:05:11.160 --> 00:05:13.860 align:middle line:84%
where we lived in our
home in Laguna Beach.

00:05:13.860 --> 00:05:15.520 align:middle line:90%
We had a grandmother's unit.

00:05:15.520 --> 00:05:18.830 align:middle line:84%
So we lived in the back
and kept our house rented.

00:05:18.830 --> 00:05:22.169 align:middle line:84%
And he got a job as
an RV mechanic at--

00:05:22.169 --> 00:05:23.710 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What a
switch, career wise.

00:05:23.710 --> 00:05:24.150 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: I know.

00:05:24.150 --> 00:05:24.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's
wonderful, though.

00:05:24.910 --> 00:05:27.140 align:middle line:84%
He had to let go,
maybe, of some ego that

00:05:27.140 --> 00:05:28.990 align:middle line:84%
had been attached to
the previous career.

00:05:28.990 --> 00:05:31.811 align:middle line:84%
Or he was done once he had hit
South America in the VW van

00:05:31.811 --> 00:05:32.310 align:middle line:90%
for a while.

00:05:32.310 --> 00:05:32.530 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.Yeah.

00:05:32.530 --> 00:05:33.280 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: Exactly.

00:05:33.280 --> 00:05:33.930 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:05:33.930 --> 00:05:35.590 align:middle line:84%
Once you're a
lawyer, you never let

00:05:35.590 --> 00:05:37.540 align:middle line:90%
go of that part, the ego part.

00:05:37.540 --> 00:05:41.260 align:middle line:84%
Because they've had
a lot of education.

00:05:41.260 --> 00:05:44.620 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, so 2 and
1/2 years later,

00:05:44.620 --> 00:05:46.850 align:middle line:84%
I started-- in the
in between time

00:05:46.850 --> 00:05:48.890 align:middle line:84%
is when I started--
people would ask

00:05:48.890 --> 00:05:52.230 align:middle line:84%
me to do their gardens because
they'd walk by the garden

00:05:52.230 --> 00:05:55.720 align:middle line:84%
that I was enthralled with,
because everything was growing

00:05:55.720 --> 00:05:57.340 align:middle line:90%
to gigantic proportions.

00:05:57.340 --> 00:05:59.120 align:middle line:90%
And they were shimmering.

00:05:59.120 --> 00:06:00.670 align:middle line:90%
And it had beautiful scent.

00:06:00.670 --> 00:06:01.920 align:middle line:90%
It was, it was fairyland.

00:06:01.920 --> 00:06:02.878 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Very magical.

00:06:02.878 --> 00:06:04.740 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: And so
I started-- people

00:06:04.740 --> 00:06:06.740 align:middle line:90%
asked me to do their gardens.

00:06:06.740 --> 00:06:08.850 align:middle line:84%
And I was like,
wow, this is great.

00:06:08.850 --> 00:06:13.800 align:middle line:84%
So that's when my landscaping
business actually started.

00:06:13.800 --> 00:06:15.960 align:middle line:84%
But then 2 and 1/2
years later, we

00:06:15.960 --> 00:06:18.150 align:middle line:90%
ended up taking our second trip.

00:06:18.150 --> 00:06:21.760 align:middle line:84%
In the second trip, we ended
up spending a major amount

00:06:21.760 --> 00:06:26.150 align:middle line:84%
of time in the national
parks and the state

00:06:26.150 --> 00:06:28.950 align:middle line:84%
parks of the United
States and Canada.

00:06:28.950 --> 00:06:32.120 align:middle line:84%
And at that point, I
knew what my passion was

00:06:32.120 --> 00:06:35.570 align:middle line:84%
and what I wanted to
do when we returned.

00:06:35.570 --> 00:06:39.130 align:middle line:84%
So I was, I'm sure,
the nature spirits

00:06:39.130 --> 00:06:42.930 align:middle line:84%
were imprinting me and
giving me information

00:06:42.930 --> 00:06:46.030 align:middle line:90%
on how to create fairy gardens.

00:06:46.030 --> 00:06:50.940 align:middle line:84%
So I, not knowing that at the
time, but when I look back,

00:06:50.940 --> 00:06:53.150 align:middle line:90%
I see how that worked.

00:06:53.150 --> 00:06:56.990 align:middle line:84%
So when I got back, I knew that
this is what I wanted to do.

00:06:56.990 --> 00:06:59.310 align:middle line:84%
But I didn't know how to
go about it, because I

00:06:59.310 --> 00:07:01.830 align:middle line:90%
didn't go to school and learn.

00:07:01.830 --> 00:07:04.070 align:middle line:84%
But I did go to the
school of Roger's Gardens

00:07:04.070 --> 00:07:07.200 align:middle line:84%
in Corona Del Mar
for three years.

00:07:07.200 --> 00:07:09.270 align:middle line:84%
They gave me a job
doing flower gardens

00:07:09.270 --> 00:07:10.930 align:middle line:90%
for their existing clients.

00:07:10.930 --> 00:07:13.850 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So how did the fairies
dovetail in with this work,

00:07:13.850 --> 00:07:15.790 align:middle line:90%
then?

00:07:15.790 --> 00:07:18.070 align:middle line:84%
Because your gardens
were different.

00:07:18.070 --> 00:07:20.750 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: Well,
after the first trip

00:07:20.750 --> 00:07:23.000 align:middle line:90%
is when I woke up spiritually.

00:07:23.000 --> 00:07:25.580 align:middle line:84%
I knew there's got
to be something

00:07:25.580 --> 00:07:30.870 align:middle line:84%
beyond the material, the
garnering of material stuff.

00:07:30.870 --> 00:07:35.430 align:middle line:84%
Because we had it all at the
age of 33, and we were nutso.

00:07:35.430 --> 00:07:38.560 align:middle line:84%
So I was like, you know, there's
something's missing here.

00:07:38.560 --> 00:07:41.500 align:middle line:84%
And I hadn't really
lived a religious,

00:07:41.500 --> 00:07:44.910 align:middle line:90%
an organized religious life.

00:07:44.910 --> 00:07:46.680 align:middle line:90%
It didn't make sense to me.

00:07:46.680 --> 00:07:48.840 align:middle line:84%
So anyway, after
the first trip, I

00:07:48.840 --> 00:07:51.050 align:middle line:84%
realized that there's
something's going on.

00:07:51.050 --> 00:07:53.780 align:middle line:84%
And I want to find
out what it is.

00:07:53.780 --> 00:07:58.190 align:middle line:84%
So two of my friends, who
didn't know each other,

00:07:58.190 --> 00:07:59.635 align:middle line:84%
suggested that I
go to this woman

00:07:59.635 --> 00:08:00.950 align:middle line:90%
and get a psychic reading.

00:08:00.950 --> 00:08:03.210 align:middle line:90%
And I'm like, wow, what's that.

00:08:03.210 --> 00:08:06.320 align:middle line:90%
So I made an appointment.

00:08:06.320 --> 00:08:10.320 align:middle line:84%
And the first thing I asked
her is do fairies exist.

00:08:10.320 --> 00:08:13.250 align:middle line:84%
And she says, "Well,
of course, my dear."

00:08:13.250 --> 00:08:16.350 align:middle line:84%
And she goes into the
library and she brings back

00:08:16.350 --> 00:08:20.830 align:middle line:84%
this book called
A True Fairy Tale

00:08:20.830 --> 00:08:22.950 align:middle line:84%
that she'd had for
many, many years.

00:08:22.950 --> 00:08:25.210 align:middle line:84%
And it was written
by Daphne Charters.

00:08:25.210 --> 00:08:28.290 align:middle line:84%
And honestly, it's the
best fairy information

00:08:28.290 --> 00:08:31.280 align:middle line:84%
I have ever found
through all my years

00:08:31.280 --> 00:08:34.600 align:middle line:84%
of searching for
fairy knowledge.

00:08:34.600 --> 00:08:42.030 align:middle line:84%
And Daphne had-- she was alive
like from the 1930s '40s,

00:08:42.030 --> 00:08:43.270 align:middle line:90%
to the '80s.

00:08:43.270 --> 00:08:46.460 align:middle line:84%
And she had a relationship
with the fairies in her garden.

00:08:46.460 --> 00:08:49.230 align:middle line:84%
And she wrote this
book, A True Fairy Tale,

00:08:49.230 --> 00:08:54.550 align:middle line:84%
that were literally
documented information

00:08:54.550 --> 00:08:59.620 align:middle line:84%
that she telepathically received
from the fairies in her garden.

00:08:59.620 --> 00:09:03.390 align:middle line:84%
And it was the fairies basically
telling the story, what they do

00:09:03.390 --> 00:09:06.990 align:middle line:84%
and how they do it, and what
their daily life is like,

00:09:06.990 --> 00:09:10.950 align:middle line:84%
and how they have relationships
and what their homes look like.

00:09:10.950 --> 00:09:12.340 align:middle line:90%
It was amazing.

00:09:12.340 --> 00:09:14.580 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Now, does that
overlay Geoffrey Hodson's

00:09:14.580 --> 00:09:16.150 align:middle line:90%
work from the 1920s?

00:09:16.150 --> 00:09:19.020 align:middle line:84%
Are there some crossovers
or similarities?

00:09:19.020 --> 00:09:21.254 align:middle line:84%
Because he's describing,
very similarly--

00:09:21.254 --> 00:09:22.670 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: Yeah
could very well be.

00:09:22.670 --> 00:09:25.450 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Their lives, what they
look like, how they interact,

00:09:25.450 --> 00:09:28.370 align:middle line:84%
the levels of intelligence
in the realms.

00:09:28.370 --> 00:09:32.220 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: Yes well, chances
are-- I mean Geoffrey Hodson's

00:09:32.220 --> 00:09:34.480 align:middle line:84%
book, I have that book,
too, and I love it.

00:09:34.480 --> 00:09:37.140 align:middle line:84%
But I haven't been able to read
it like I've been able to read

00:09:37.140 --> 00:09:37.700 align:middle line:90%
Daphne's.

00:09:37.700 --> 00:09:37.880 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I see.

00:09:37.880 --> 00:09:39.296 align:middle line:84%
There's a different
quality to it.

00:09:39.296 --> 00:09:40.971 align:middle line:90%
I'd love to read it.

00:09:40.971 --> 00:09:41.470 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:09:41.470 --> 00:09:43.690 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: Well, she's passed on.

00:09:43.690 --> 00:09:46.440 align:middle line:84%
And the original book
my teacher Gladys

00:09:46.440 --> 00:09:49.250 align:middle line:90%
gave me was printed in the '50s.

00:09:49.250 --> 00:09:51.540 align:middle line:84%
And it's just like the
most treasured thing I own.

00:09:51.540 --> 00:09:52.950 align:middle line:90%
And it's falling apart.

00:09:52.950 --> 00:09:55.920 align:middle line:84%
But interestingly
enough, she handed

00:09:55.920 --> 00:10:02.520 align:middle line:84%
over her writings and her
experiences to a gentleman

00:10:02.520 --> 00:10:04.590 align:middle line:90%
by the name of Michael Pilarski.

00:10:04.590 --> 00:10:08.775 align:middle line:84%
And in my book, I recommend
that people get that book

00:10:08.775 --> 00:10:13.880 align:middle line:84%
if they want a more in-depth
knowledge of the fairy realm.

00:10:13.880 --> 00:10:21.320 align:middle line:84%
And he got all of her writings,
which is like 3/4 more

00:10:21.320 --> 00:10:22.960 align:middle line:90%
than the original book.

00:10:22.960 --> 00:10:27.359 align:middle line:84%
And it's called 40 Years With
the Fairies by Daphne Charters.

00:10:27.359 --> 00:10:27.900 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:10:27.900 --> 00:10:30.670 align:middle line:90%
So I have to get that one.

00:10:30.670 --> 00:10:31.990 align:middle line:90%
These books are magical.

00:10:31.990 --> 00:10:35.920 align:middle line:84%
And these people are very
credible seers of their day.

00:10:35.920 --> 00:10:38.230 align:middle line:90%
This is not a hallucination.

00:10:38.230 --> 00:10:39.030 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: Exactly.

00:10:39.030 --> 00:10:39.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: There
are brains that are

00:10:39.910 --> 00:10:41.700 align:middle line:84%
wired for seeing
into other realms.

00:10:41.700 --> 00:10:44.880 align:middle line:84%
And these people are able to
see into these other realms,

00:10:44.880 --> 00:10:46.860 align:middle line:84%
and so they brought
back the documentation.

00:10:46.860 --> 00:10:51.370 align:middle line:84%
Now for you, you were able
to feel into the other realms

00:10:51.370 --> 00:10:52.510 align:middle line:90%
and receive information.

00:10:52.510 --> 00:10:55.540 align:middle line:84%
But you were kind of
frustrated that, why can't, I

00:10:55.540 --> 00:10:56.350 align:middle line:90%
can feel you.

00:10:56.350 --> 00:10:57.680 align:middle line:90%
I'm interacting with you.

00:10:57.680 --> 00:10:59.460 align:middle line:84%
I'm downloading
your information.

00:10:59.460 --> 00:11:00.659 align:middle line:90%
But you couldn't see them.

00:11:00.659 --> 00:11:01.200 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: No.

00:11:01.200 --> 00:11:03.880 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And so,
you brokered a deal

00:11:03.880 --> 00:11:05.920 align:middle line:84%
when you were told to
write your fairy book.

00:11:05.920 --> 00:11:07.710 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: Exactly.

00:11:07.710 --> 00:11:12.720 align:middle line:84%
Well, after 25 years
of doing gardens

00:11:12.720 --> 00:11:17.840 align:middle line:84%
in Orange County, California,
I kept asking god, goddess,

00:11:17.840 --> 00:11:22.180 align:middle line:84%
all that is, OK, how many
more gardens do I have to do.

00:11:22.180 --> 00:11:26.200 align:middle line:84%
So I finally got the
download to leave,

00:11:26.200 --> 00:11:28.540 align:middle line:84%
because I wanted to
move to the Sedona area.

00:11:28.540 --> 00:11:31.230 align:middle line:84%
I knew that this was
where I was going.

00:11:31.230 --> 00:11:34.690 align:middle line:90%
And I retired.

00:11:34.690 --> 00:11:36.740 align:middle line:84%
And I got there and
I was sitting around.

00:11:36.740 --> 00:11:41.050 align:middle line:84%
And the fairies came to me
and asked me to do a book.

00:11:41.050 --> 00:11:45.820 align:middle line:90%
And I said no, I'm not a writer.

00:11:45.820 --> 00:11:47.110 align:middle line:90%
Don't want to go there.

00:11:47.110 --> 00:11:49.390 align:middle line:84%
Not ready to step
on the world stage

00:11:49.390 --> 00:11:51.502 align:middle line:90%
and deliver fairy information.

00:11:51.502 --> 00:11:54.204 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I'd rather
keep it private.

00:11:54.204 --> 00:11:55.870 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: I didn't
really want everybody

00:11:55.870 --> 00:11:58.200 align:middle line:84%
to know what goes on
in my mind, you know,

00:11:58.200 --> 00:12:01.340 align:middle line:90%
and how I deal with fairy life.

00:12:01.340 --> 00:12:05.730 align:middle line:84%
So after about three times,
I finally acquiesced.

00:12:05.730 --> 00:12:07.520 align:middle line:90%
I said OK fine.

00:12:07.520 --> 00:12:09.140 align:middle line:90%
I'll make a deal with you.

00:12:09.140 --> 00:12:14.290 align:middle line:84%
If you will show yourself
through the lens of my camera,

00:12:14.290 --> 00:12:15.630 align:middle line:90%
I'll do that for you.

00:12:15.630 --> 00:12:17.010 align:middle line:90%
I'll do the book.

00:12:17.010 --> 00:12:21.710 align:middle line:84%
So honestly, the first
photo of the last garden

00:12:21.710 --> 00:12:25.880 align:middle line:84%
I did in Orange County, a flying
fairy shows up with a wand.

00:12:25.880 --> 00:12:27.590 align:middle line:90%
So then I was committed.

00:12:27.590 --> 00:12:29.260 align:middle line:84%
So I had to learn--
then I had to learn

00:12:29.260 --> 00:12:34.490 align:middle line:84%
to be a writer, and
self-publish, and a promoter.

00:12:34.490 --> 00:12:37.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And it's interesting
because when you're

00:12:37.910 --> 00:12:40.940 align:middle line:84%
looking at images, some
of the fairy images

00:12:40.940 --> 00:12:43.140 align:middle line:84%
that you've captured,
and some of the things

00:12:43.140 --> 00:12:44.970 align:middle line:84%
you have in your
book, some of them

00:12:44.970 --> 00:12:50.850 align:middle line:84%
are like light figures that are
appearing in front of water,

00:12:50.850 --> 00:12:52.690 align:middle line:84%
in front of flowers
or landscapes.

00:12:52.690 --> 00:12:55.520 align:middle line:84%
And some of them are
obvious like Wizard of Oz,

00:12:55.520 --> 00:12:57.370 align:middle line:90%
like trees with faces.

00:12:57.370 --> 00:13:02.200 align:middle line:84%
Like, in Sedona for example,
those amazing gnome-like

00:13:02.200 --> 00:13:05.930 align:middle line:84%
faces that look like gigantic,
good natured entities

00:13:05.930 --> 00:13:07.270 align:middle line:90%
that are overlooking the land.

00:13:07.270 --> 00:13:09.853 align:middle line:84%
And anyone who spends a lot of
time out on the land in Sedona,

00:13:09.853 --> 00:13:11.310 align:middle line:90%
you can feel these beings.

00:13:11.310 --> 00:13:12.110 align:middle line:90%
You can feel them.

00:13:12.110 --> 00:13:14.360 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: Well, when I
started on this quest,

00:13:14.360 --> 00:13:16.110 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know what
they looked like.

00:13:16.110 --> 00:13:21.920 align:middle line:84%
So what happened is,
I went into meditation

00:13:21.920 --> 00:13:25.710 align:middle line:84%
and asked them to
please reveal themselves

00:13:25.710 --> 00:13:27.510 align:middle line:90%
in the lens of my camera.

00:13:27.510 --> 00:13:30.550 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't know, I had no
clue what they looked like.

00:13:30.550 --> 00:13:32.380 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I've seen orbs.

00:13:32.380 --> 00:13:34.830 align:middle line:84%
And many of us have seen
those in our photographs.

00:13:34.830 --> 00:13:37.780 align:middle line:84%
And I believe that that's
their natural state.

00:13:37.780 --> 00:13:42.200 align:middle line:84%
So I just intuited going through
the garden where one of them

00:13:42.200 --> 00:13:43.170 align:middle line:90%
might be.

00:13:43.170 --> 00:13:46.540 align:middle line:84%
So I would take a picture
here and take a photo there.

00:13:46.540 --> 00:13:49.090 align:middle line:84%
And then I'd go
back to my computer,

00:13:49.090 --> 00:13:50.720 align:middle line:90%
put the chip into the computer.

00:13:50.720 --> 00:13:52.710 align:middle line:90%
And then I'd study them.

00:13:52.710 --> 00:13:56.250 align:middle line:84%
And interestingly enough,
at first I didn't see them.

00:13:56.250 --> 00:14:00.980 align:middle line:84%
But then as I just kept
at it and at it and at it,

00:14:00.980 --> 00:14:03.150 align:middle line:84%
they started revealing
themselves to me

00:14:03.150 --> 00:14:06.330 align:middle line:84%
in the photographs, some of
which you will see today.

00:14:06.330 --> 00:14:12.660 align:middle line:84%
And what I found is
that they're hiding

00:14:12.660 --> 00:14:16.400 align:middle line:84%
in plain sight, which
is really remarkable.

00:14:16.400 --> 00:14:20.520 align:middle line:84%
It's just that our
visual is so linear.

00:14:20.520 --> 00:14:24.000 align:middle line:84%
But once you see them in
photographs, then what happens

00:14:24.000 --> 00:14:28.450 align:middle line:84%
is your awareness expands
and then your sight expands.

00:14:28.450 --> 00:14:33.300 align:middle line:84%
And my purpose of asking them
to show up in the photographs

00:14:33.300 --> 00:14:36.400 align:middle line:84%
is because I have read
almost every single book

00:14:36.400 --> 00:14:42.500 align:middle line:84%
on fairies known to womankind,
or my kind, humankind,

00:14:42.500 --> 00:14:43.930 align:middle line:90%
and mankind.

00:14:43.930 --> 00:14:47.020 align:middle line:84%
And I have never seen
a photograph of one.

00:14:47.020 --> 00:14:49.840 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, you know,
I've seen drawings,

00:14:49.840 --> 00:14:53.600 align:middle line:84%
like in Geoffrey Hodson's book,
and even in Daphne Charter's

00:14:53.600 --> 00:14:59.200 align:middle line:84%
book 40 Years With the Fairies,
they've got drawings in there.

00:14:59.200 --> 00:15:02.760 align:middle line:84%
So I feel what's so
pertinent in the book

00:15:02.760 --> 00:15:06.610 align:middle line:84%
that I've co-created with the
fairies is that they showed up

00:15:06.610 --> 00:15:07.830 align:middle line:90%
in physicality.

00:15:07.830 --> 00:15:09.900 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And it's
all items of nature.

00:15:09.900 --> 00:15:11.380 align:middle line:90%
Some of them can be very dense.

00:15:11.380 --> 00:15:13.630 align:middle line:84%
They can be the mineral
kingdom, where you simply

00:15:13.630 --> 00:15:15.210 align:middle line:90%
see the face shining through.

00:15:15.210 --> 00:15:19.000 align:middle line:84%
Or they can be as fleeting
as a little sprite that's

00:15:19.000 --> 00:15:20.850 align:middle line:84%
at the water, when
the water is moving.

00:15:20.850 --> 00:15:21.600 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: Exactly.

00:15:21.600 --> 00:15:22.760 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And this
is a part-- this

00:15:22.760 --> 00:15:24.650 align:middle line:84%
is where people have
trouble with fairies.

00:15:24.650 --> 00:15:28.670 align:middle line:90%
They think it's a rock.

00:15:28.670 --> 00:15:30.050 align:middle line:90%
So what if it looks like a face.

00:15:30.050 --> 00:15:32.180 align:middle line:84%
It's just coincidental
it looks like that.

00:15:32.180 --> 00:15:33.000 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: It's not.

00:15:33.000 --> 00:15:35.390 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's just the
tree looks like a face.

00:15:35.390 --> 00:15:36.610 align:middle line:90%
It's coincidental.

00:15:36.610 --> 00:15:38.930 align:middle line:84%
And that's what people
who are naysayers

00:15:38.930 --> 00:15:41.200 align:middle line:84%
when it comes to
fairies would say.

00:15:41.200 --> 00:15:44.460 align:middle line:84%
Is that, yeah, well you can
make a face in anything.

00:15:44.460 --> 00:15:47.160 align:middle line:90%
Tell them why that isn't so.

00:15:47.160 --> 00:15:50.490 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: Well, I choose
to call them nature spirits

00:15:50.490 --> 00:15:55.880 align:middle line:84%
because fairies are an aspect
of the nature spirit realm.

00:15:55.880 --> 00:16:01.570 align:middle line:84%
So if you see a rock with a face
in it, it is actually a gnome.

00:16:01.570 --> 00:16:04.950 align:middle line:84%
And if you see an
angel in the clouds,

00:16:04.950 --> 00:16:06.830 align:middle line:90%
that's considered a fairy.

00:16:06.830 --> 00:16:12.170 align:middle line:84%
And the fairies and the gnomes,
and all of the nature spirits

00:16:12.170 --> 00:16:17.210 align:middle line:84%
are an aspect, or an
evolutionary aspect

00:16:17.210 --> 00:16:19.180 align:middle line:90%
of the angelic realm.

00:16:19.180 --> 00:16:26.370 align:middle line:84%
So they are literally the worker
bees of the angelic realm.

00:16:26.370 --> 00:16:29.260 align:middle line:84%
And they have an
evolution that they

00:16:29.260 --> 00:16:32.840 align:middle line:90%
follow through divine will.

00:16:32.840 --> 00:16:34.590 align:middle line:84%
I learned a lot of
this information

00:16:34.590 --> 00:16:37.920 align:middle line:84%
through Daphne Charter's work,
because the fairies actually

00:16:37.920 --> 00:16:41.470 align:middle line:84%
were letting her know
what their job is.

00:16:41.470 --> 00:16:43.330 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I want to
ask you to go through.

00:16:43.330 --> 00:16:45.210 align:middle line:84%
I just wanted you
to address that.

00:16:45.210 --> 00:16:48.270 align:middle line:84%
Because someone who's
skeptical about this would say,

00:16:48.270 --> 00:16:49.270 align:middle line:90%
it's a rock.

00:16:49.270 --> 00:16:51.120 align:middle line:84%
It just happens to
look like a face.

00:16:51.120 --> 00:16:55.690 align:middle line:84%
And from the work of Hodson, of
Daphne, of yourself and others,

00:16:55.690 --> 00:16:56.770 align:middle line:90%
no, that's not true.

00:16:56.770 --> 00:16:58.145 align:middle line:84%
It appears that
way for a reason.

00:16:58.145 --> 00:17:00.594 align:middle line:84%
There's intelligence
that fashions everything.

00:17:00.594 --> 00:17:01.760 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: This is very true.

00:17:01.760 --> 00:17:03.926 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And that's the
point that we need to make.

00:17:03.926 --> 00:17:06.710 align:middle line:84%
So I want to start out
on the fairy realm,

00:17:06.710 --> 00:17:09.990 align:middle line:84%
starting with the microscopic
little fairies and the nature

00:17:09.990 --> 00:17:11.720 align:middle line:84%
of them and their
evolutionary path.

00:17:11.720 --> 00:17:13.180 align:middle line:84%
And then we'll go
into the more--

00:17:13.180 --> 00:17:15.150 align:middle line:84%
we'll go into the more
recognizable ones.

00:17:15.150 --> 00:17:17.569 align:middle line:84%
But before we do that, you
mention in your book someone--

00:17:17.569 --> 00:17:19.839 align:middle line:90%
a being called Lord Kuthumi.

00:17:19.839 --> 00:17:21.460 align:middle line:90%
Who is Lord Kuthumi?

00:17:21.460 --> 00:17:25.640 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: Well, in
creating this book,

00:17:25.640 --> 00:17:29.570 align:middle line:84%
I got the download
on some level,

00:17:29.570 --> 00:17:31.830 align:middle line:84%
to communicate with
the nature spirits

00:17:31.830 --> 00:17:36.750 align:middle line:84%
in the photographs that came
through the lens of my camera.

00:17:36.750 --> 00:17:40.280 align:middle line:90%
So I decided well, I'll try it.

00:17:40.280 --> 00:17:43.494 align:middle line:84%
You know, I've never really
channeled that much before.

00:17:43.494 --> 00:17:44.910 align:middle line:84%
And I thought well,
I'm just going

00:17:44.910 --> 00:17:46.800 align:middle line:84%
to ask them and
see what happens.

00:17:46.800 --> 00:17:47.870 align:middle line:90%
And it was amazing.

00:17:47.870 --> 00:17:51.010 align:middle line:84%
I had these telepathic
communications with them.

00:17:51.010 --> 00:17:53.540 align:middle line:84%
And on one of the
communications,

00:17:53.540 --> 00:17:56.432 align:middle line:90%
it was of Pan, who is an over--

00:17:56.432 --> 00:17:57.015 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Pan.

00:17:57.015 --> 00:17:57.515 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:17:57.515 --> 00:17:58.120 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: Pan.

00:17:58.120 --> 00:18:00.720 align:middle line:90%
One of the demigods of nature.

00:18:00.720 --> 00:18:04.690 align:middle line:84%
And his job is to
oversee agriculture

00:18:04.690 --> 00:18:10.890 align:middle line:84%
and to also oversee the herds of
animals, as in sheep and cows,

00:18:10.890 --> 00:18:13.720 align:middle line:84%
to make sure they don't
overlap one another.

00:18:13.720 --> 00:18:18.391 align:middle line:84%
And he also communicates with
all the different nature spirit

00:18:18.391 --> 00:18:18.890 align:middle line:90%
realms.

00:18:18.890 --> 00:18:24.740 align:middle line:84%
So I asked him in channeling,
or telepathic communication

00:18:24.740 --> 00:18:27.230 align:middle line:90%
with him, well who do you go to.

00:18:27.230 --> 00:18:29.830 align:middle line:90%
And he told me Lord Kutumi.

00:18:29.830 --> 00:18:32.030 align:middle line:84%
And I thought-- I'd
never read that.

00:18:32.030 --> 00:18:34.010 align:middle line:90%
I had never seen it anywhere.

00:18:34.010 --> 00:18:37.320 align:middle line:84%
So I just trusted that
that was accurate.

00:18:37.320 --> 00:18:42.110 align:middle line:84%
So Lord Kutumi,
through my exploration,

00:18:42.110 --> 00:18:46.690 align:middle line:84%
is apparently the
over-lighting being

00:18:46.690 --> 00:18:51.669 align:middle line:84%
that takes care of all
the nature spirits.

00:18:51.669 --> 00:18:52.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:18:52.210 --> 00:18:54.260 align:middle line:84%
So and from there,
then the download

00:18:54.260 --> 00:18:56.510 align:middle line:84%
started as to the nature
of some of these beings.

00:18:56.510 --> 00:18:58.520 align:middle line:90%
And also, your research into it.

00:18:58.520 --> 00:19:02.430 align:middle line:84%
So give us an idea of what the
most minute little beings there

00:19:02.430 --> 00:19:03.230 align:middle line:90%
are like.

00:19:03.230 --> 00:19:06.340 align:middle line:84%
And then we'll start
graduating into gnomes

00:19:06.340 --> 00:19:07.721 align:middle line:90%
and elves and fairies and on.

00:19:07.721 --> 00:19:08.262 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: OK.

00:19:08.262 --> 00:19:13.540 align:middle line:84%
Well, I learned that the
Rudimes are the initial stage

00:19:13.540 --> 00:19:16.040 align:middle line:84%
of the fairy-- I
mean, the whole nature

00:19:16.040 --> 00:19:18.360 align:middle line:90%
spirit angelic evolution.

00:19:18.360 --> 00:19:20.000 align:middle line:90%
And they are like insects.

00:19:20.000 --> 00:19:23.140 align:middle line:84%
If you look up into a blue
sky-- not into the sun,

00:19:23.140 --> 00:19:26.580 align:middle line:84%
but into a blue sky-- if
you just stare up there,

00:19:26.580 --> 00:19:27.549 align:middle line:90%
you'll see like--

00:19:27.549 --> 00:19:29.090 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Those
sparkling white bits.

00:19:29.090 --> 00:19:30.560 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: You'll see white bits.

00:19:30.560 --> 00:19:34.280 align:middle line:84%
And you'll also see like,
insect-like movements.

00:19:34.280 --> 00:19:37.790 align:middle line:84%
And also, when you look
on a lake, or on a river,

00:19:37.790 --> 00:19:41.987 align:middle line:84%
on the ocean, and you see those
beautiful sparkles of sunlight.

00:19:41.987 --> 00:19:42.570 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:19:42.570 --> 00:19:44.028 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: Those
are nature spirits.

00:19:44.028 --> 00:19:44.760 align:middle line:90%
Isn't that magic?

00:19:44.760 --> 00:19:45.676 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Interesting.

00:19:45.676 --> 00:19:46.530 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: I know.

00:19:46.530 --> 00:19:48.040 align:middle line:90%
I just love that.

00:19:48.040 --> 00:19:50.880 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, so they just
live a very short while.

00:19:50.880 --> 00:19:54.070 align:middle line:84%
And then they leave this
plane of demonstration

00:19:54.070 --> 00:19:56.300 align:middle line:90%
and go into the etheric realm.

00:19:56.300 --> 00:19:57.560 align:middle line:90%
And they go to school.

00:19:57.560 --> 00:20:01.760 align:middle line:84%
And then they come back as the
next evolution of nature spirit

00:20:01.760 --> 00:20:04.360 align:middle line:90%
angelic.

00:20:04.360 --> 00:20:06.336 align:middle line:84%
And then they live
on this plane.

00:20:06.336 --> 00:20:07.210 align:middle line:90%
And they do the work.

00:20:07.210 --> 00:20:08.760 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And they're like, I
remember reading in the book,

00:20:08.760 --> 00:20:10.450 align:middle line:84%
they're anywhere from
an 1/8 of an inch,

00:20:10.450 --> 00:20:12.585 align:middle line:84%
those little tiny sparkles
you first spoke of,

00:20:12.585 --> 00:20:15.260 align:middle line:84%
the little insect-like
ones, up to 1/2 an inch.

00:20:15.260 --> 00:20:16.720 align:middle line:84%
And then keep
growing from there.

00:20:16.720 --> 00:20:16.980 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:20:16.980 --> 00:20:17.604 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: Yeah.

00:20:17.604 --> 00:20:22.490 align:middle line:84%
See, their job is that
they infuse energy coming

00:20:22.490 --> 00:20:25.880 align:middle line:84%
from our sun, which
looks like the rainbow.

00:20:25.880 --> 00:20:28.800 align:middle line:84%
When we see a rainbow,
you see all these colors

00:20:28.800 --> 00:20:30.030 align:middle line:90%
falling to earth.

00:20:30.030 --> 00:20:32.940 align:middle line:84%
Well those colors are
always falling to the earth.

00:20:32.940 --> 00:20:38.540 align:middle line:84%
So their job is to learn
to infuse that energetic

00:20:38.540 --> 00:20:41.680 align:middle line:84%
and expel it out
to their charges.

00:20:41.680 --> 00:20:46.190 align:middle line:84%
So once they've mastered each
evolution of the nature spirit

00:20:46.190 --> 00:20:48.910 align:middle line:84%
realm, going all the
way up to archangel,

00:20:48.910 --> 00:20:52.520 align:middle line:90%
they go back to the other side.

00:20:52.520 --> 00:20:55.680 align:middle line:84%
They go to the other side,
just like we do when we pass.

00:20:55.680 --> 00:20:57.400 align:middle line:90%
We shed our physical vehicle.

00:20:57.400 --> 00:20:59.060 align:middle line:90%
We go to the other side.

00:20:59.060 --> 00:21:00.620 align:middle line:90%
We go to the halls of learning.

00:21:00.620 --> 00:21:09.140 align:middle line:84%
We learn our next focus of
what we desire to experience.

00:21:09.140 --> 00:21:11.040 align:middle line:90%
And so, they do the same thing.

00:21:11.040 --> 00:21:13.290 align:middle line:90%
So by the time--

00:21:13.290 --> 00:21:15.360 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: As they say,
as above so below.

00:21:15.360 --> 00:21:15.715 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: Exactly.

00:21:15.715 --> 00:21:16.315 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Everything
we go through

00:21:16.315 --> 00:21:18.410 align:middle line:84%
is reflected throughout
all of nature,

00:21:18.410 --> 00:21:21.326 align:middle line:84%
right up to the size
of the cosmos itself.

00:21:21.326 --> 00:21:22.450 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: That's very true.

00:21:22.450 --> 00:21:23.260 align:middle line:90%
It's very true.

00:21:23.260 --> 00:21:24.520 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So these
tiny little beings

00:21:24.520 --> 00:21:25.560 align:middle line:90%
are going through this as well.

00:21:25.560 --> 00:21:27.351 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: They go
through the same process.

00:21:27.351 --> 00:21:30.791 align:middle line:84%
And then they will
evolve to being--

00:21:30.791 --> 00:21:34.100 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Let's say
to-- the little minutes,

00:21:34.100 --> 00:21:35.860 align:middle line:84%
those are tiny
little things again.

00:21:35.860 --> 00:21:38.150 align:middle line:84%
But by the time
you get to gnomes,

00:21:38.150 --> 00:21:41.061 align:middle line:90%
these are more sizable beings.

00:21:41.061 --> 00:21:41.560 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:21:41.560 --> 00:21:43.930 align:middle line:84%
Anywhere from like six
to eighteen inches.

00:21:43.930 --> 00:21:47.230 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: Yeah many
people have seen them.

00:21:47.230 --> 00:21:50.700 align:middle line:84%
And they work in the earth,
you know, like in Snow White

00:21:50.700 --> 00:21:52.610 align:middle line:90%
and her dwarfs.

00:21:52.610 --> 00:21:54.950 align:middle line:84%
The dwarfs and
gnomes and trolls,

00:21:54.950 --> 00:21:59.230 align:middle line:84%
they're all sort of of
the same earth matrix.

00:21:59.230 --> 00:22:00.150 align:middle line:90%
Let's put it that way.

00:22:00.150 --> 00:22:03.154 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Disney was apparently
quite tapped into the mystical.

00:22:03.154 --> 00:22:04.320 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: He must have been.

00:22:04.320 --> 00:22:07.410 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: When he did these
various films for animation,

00:22:07.410 --> 00:22:10.312 align:middle line:84%
he was actually drawing
on-- and I know in Hodson,

00:22:10.312 --> 00:22:11.520 align:middle line:90%
I haven't read Daphne's book.

00:22:11.520 --> 00:22:13.800 align:middle line:84%
I only have these to go by,
because I love his books.

00:22:13.800 --> 00:22:16.030 align:middle line:84%
Hodson's books about
the fairies and the way

00:22:16.030 --> 00:22:18.300 align:middle line:84%
he's describing them
back in the '20s-- when

00:22:18.300 --> 00:22:21.600 align:middle line:84%
he'd go into the forest and
this information would come

00:22:21.600 --> 00:22:26.840 align:middle line:84%
through him-- is very similar to
what people in different lands

00:22:26.840 --> 00:22:28.200 align:middle line:90%
characterize.

00:22:28.200 --> 00:22:31.730 align:middle line:84%
And I always found it
amusing that-- why not,

00:22:31.730 --> 00:22:37.300 align:middle line:84%
we wear clothes-- that these
little brownies and dwarfs that

00:22:37.300 --> 00:22:39.980 align:middle line:84%
work with the trees and
the grass and the land,

00:22:39.980 --> 00:22:41.970 align:middle line:84%
and come out of the
bark, have their little--

00:22:41.970 --> 00:22:43.006 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: They have
their own look.

00:22:43.006 --> 00:22:43.362 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:22:43.362 --> 00:22:43.987 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:22:43.987 --> 00:22:45.290 align:middle line:90%
They have their little coats.

00:22:45.290 --> 00:22:46.540 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: They have
their own style.

00:22:46.540 --> 00:22:48.170 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They have
their own style.

00:22:48.170 --> 00:22:50.620 align:middle line:84%
And let's talk about the
levels of consciousness,

00:22:50.620 --> 00:22:52.770 align:middle line:84%
because I found that
fascinating, too.

00:22:52.770 --> 00:22:56.160 align:middle line:84%
Not all of these beings are
as intelligent or conscious

00:22:56.160 --> 00:22:58.150 align:middle line:90%
as some of the others.

00:22:58.150 --> 00:23:00.420 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: No, because it's
an evolutionary process.

00:23:00.420 --> 00:23:05.350 align:middle line:84%
So you know, when they're
learning to be gnomes,

00:23:05.350 --> 00:23:07.830 align:middle line:84%
or when they come
here to be gnomes,

00:23:07.830 --> 00:23:09.540 align:middle line:84%
they're working with
the earth elements.

00:23:09.540 --> 00:23:11.490 align:middle line:84%
And they're bringing
the nutrients

00:23:11.490 --> 00:23:14.010 align:middle line:84%
to the roots of the
trees and to the water

00:23:14.010 --> 00:23:16.481 align:middle line:90%
and to the mineral kingdom.

00:23:16.481 --> 00:23:18.980 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So the ones you have
in your book of the red rock,

00:23:18.980 --> 00:23:23.330 align:middle line:84%
the huge rocks, the huge rock
face, and also the tree face,

00:23:23.330 --> 00:23:24.960 align:middle line:84%
those would be
considered gnomes?

00:23:24.960 --> 00:23:25.880 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: They would.

00:23:25.880 --> 00:23:26.380 align:middle line:90%
They would.

00:23:26.380 --> 00:23:31.100 align:middle line:84%
Because they're holding the
form of the rock or the mineral

00:23:31.100 --> 00:23:32.150 align:middle line:90%
kingdom.

00:23:32.150 --> 00:23:34.400 align:middle line:84%
So yeah, can you imagine
that kind of a lifetime?

00:23:34.400 --> 00:23:35.560 align:middle line:90%
How many years?

00:23:35.560 --> 00:23:37.580 align:middle line:84%
How many millenniums
you'd be sitting

00:23:37.580 --> 00:23:38.726 align:middle line:90%
there holding that energy.

00:23:38.726 --> 00:23:39.350 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:23:39.350 --> 00:23:40.600 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:23:40.600 --> 00:23:42.340 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: So that's their job.

00:23:42.340 --> 00:23:44.390 align:middle line:90%
And then they evolve to fairies.

00:23:44.390 --> 00:23:47.600 align:middle line:84%
And when they go
to the other side,

00:23:47.600 --> 00:23:49.380 align:middle line:84%
they learn about
how to be a fairy.

00:23:49.380 --> 00:23:54.900 align:middle line:84%
Then they get to choose, for the
first time in their evolution,

00:23:54.900 --> 00:23:57.870 align:middle line:84%
about what they want to
do, meaning the focus,

00:23:57.870 --> 00:24:02.500 align:middle line:84%
whether they want to be air,
earth, fire, water fairy

00:24:02.500 --> 00:24:04.870 align:middle line:90%
or, you know, nature spirit.

00:24:04.870 --> 00:24:09.120 align:middle line:10%
And also, it's the first time
they learn about suffering,

00:24:09.120 --> 00:24:12.870 align:middle line:10%
which I thought was very
interesting, because we,

00:24:12.870 --> 00:24:16.370 align:middle line:10%
as spiritual beings
having a human experience,

00:24:16.370 --> 00:24:20.460 align:middle line:10%
we have nature
spirits supporting us.

00:24:20.460 --> 00:24:23.390 align:middle line:84%
Fairies, there house fairies,
there are people fairies,

00:24:23.390 --> 00:24:27.492 align:middle line:84%
there are river fairies, there
are garden, flower fairies.

00:24:27.492 --> 00:24:28.950 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We have
constant support.

00:24:28.950 --> 00:24:32.450 align:middle line:84%
Plus, the archangelic realm
and the angelic realm.

00:24:32.450 --> 00:24:33.530 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: So yeah.

00:24:33.530 --> 00:24:36.100 align:middle line:84%
So they have to experience
suffering so that they

00:24:36.100 --> 00:24:38.670 align:middle line:90%
know about the human condition.

00:24:38.670 --> 00:24:40.460 align:middle line:84%
And they know about
the animal condition,

00:24:40.460 --> 00:24:42.400 align:middle line:90%
because animals suffer, too.

00:24:42.400 --> 00:24:45.300 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sure, the mineral
kingdom suffers on some level

00:24:45.300 --> 00:24:46.320 align:middle line:90%
as well.

00:24:46.320 --> 00:24:47.299 align:middle line:90%
So it's interesting.

00:24:47.299 --> 00:24:48.840 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And those
are depicted more

00:24:48.840 --> 00:24:50.390 align:middle line:90%
like Tinkerbell in Peter Pan.

00:24:50.390 --> 00:24:51.098 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: Mm-hmm.

00:24:51.098 --> 00:24:51.987 align:middle line:90%
They are.

00:24:51.987 --> 00:24:54.070 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The fairies are
a little larger in size.

00:24:54.070 --> 00:24:55.486 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: But they
look different.

00:24:55.486 --> 00:24:58.490 align:middle line:84%
I mean, as I said, I didn't
know what they look like.

00:24:58.490 --> 00:25:02.530 align:middle line:84%
And so I have found that--
and I may have said this--

00:25:02.530 --> 00:25:04.759 align:middle line:84%
they're literally
hiding in plain sight.

00:25:04.759 --> 00:25:06.300 align:middle line:84%
So once you become
aware of what they

00:25:06.300 --> 00:25:09.435 align:middle line:84%
look like, you will start seeing
them, which is so exciting.

00:25:09.435 --> 00:25:12.000 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You've captured a
couple of them in the book.

00:25:12.000 --> 00:25:14.630 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: And this is what
I was so excited about,

00:25:14.630 --> 00:25:16.690 align:middle line:84%
was to be able to have
photographs of them.

00:25:16.690 --> 00:25:17.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:25:17.430 --> 00:25:18.610 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: So anyway, it's--

00:25:18.610 --> 00:25:19.765 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And then
you have-- I like what

00:25:19.765 --> 00:25:22.260 align:middle line:84%
you did, in that you had little
line drawings next to it.

00:25:22.260 --> 00:25:25.230 align:middle line:84%
So for people that don't
do pattern association

00:25:25.230 --> 00:25:28.690 align:middle line:84%
or their brains don't
work in an abstract way,

00:25:28.690 --> 00:25:32.210 align:middle line:84%
you can look at it, then go back
and look at it again and see

00:25:32.210 --> 00:25:34.690 align:middle line:84%
where that is, where
that is hiding there.

00:25:34.690 --> 00:25:37.100 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER:I felt that was
absolutely necessary when

00:25:37.100 --> 00:25:38.920 align:middle line:84%
showing the photographs,
because, I mean,

00:25:38.920 --> 00:25:41.050 align:middle line:90%
I instantly see it now.

00:25:41.050 --> 00:25:43.520 align:middle line:84%
As I said, at first I didn't
know what I was looking for.

00:25:43.520 --> 00:25:45.370 align:middle line:84%
And then it was like,
wow, there it is.

00:25:45.370 --> 00:25:46.460 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, by
the end of the book

00:25:46.460 --> 00:25:48.160 align:middle line:84%
you start, even just
reading through your book,

00:25:48.160 --> 00:25:49.960 align:middle line:84%
you start seeing the
patterns much more quickly.

00:25:49.960 --> 00:25:50.626 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER:Mm-hmm.

00:25:50.626 --> 00:25:51.440 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:25:51.440 --> 00:25:54.770 align:middle line:84%
So some people have
difficulty even seeing things.

00:25:54.770 --> 00:25:57.390 align:middle line:84%
But then the other
thing I noticed,

00:25:57.390 --> 00:25:59.780 align:middle line:84%
everybody sees
something different.

00:25:59.780 --> 00:26:02.630 align:middle line:84%
And through the evolution
of these photographs,

00:26:02.630 --> 00:26:04.630 align:middle line:84%
even though the book's
been out for a few years,

00:26:04.630 --> 00:26:06.460 align:middle line:84%
I will look at these
photographs sometimes

00:26:06.460 --> 00:26:08.930 align:middle line:84%
and see something I've
never seen before.

00:26:08.930 --> 00:26:13.190 align:middle line:84%
So I think that they play with
us, too, and reveal themselves,

00:26:13.190 --> 00:26:14.580 align:middle line:90%
which is fascinating.

00:26:14.580 --> 00:26:16.050 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:26:16.050 --> 00:26:16.550 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:26:16.550 --> 00:26:18.730 align:middle line:84%
So we were talking
about fairies.

00:26:18.730 --> 00:26:21.200 align:middle line:84%
That's where a little bit
of free will comes in.

00:26:21.200 --> 00:26:26.100 align:middle line:84%
And they can go into any of the
realms, again, that they wish,

00:26:26.100 --> 00:26:27.910 align:middle line:90%
and start expressing themselves.

00:26:27.910 --> 00:26:30.520 align:middle line:84%
And they have a much longer
lifespan by this time.

00:26:30.520 --> 00:26:31.600 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: Exactly.

00:26:31.600 --> 00:26:33.840 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, they do.

00:26:33.840 --> 00:26:39.390 align:middle line:84%
They actually stay until they've
mastered whatever the focus is.

00:26:39.390 --> 00:26:44.320 align:middle line:84%
And they don't necessarily have
a physical form like we do.

00:26:44.320 --> 00:26:47.610 align:middle line:90%
But they can-- they showed up.

00:26:47.610 --> 00:26:50.180 align:middle line:84%
They showed up in the
photographs in forms

00:26:50.180 --> 00:26:53.250 align:middle line:90%
that I could associate with.

00:26:53.250 --> 00:26:55.010 align:middle line:84%
I may have said
this, but I think

00:26:55.010 --> 00:26:59.870 align:middle line:84%
their normal form
is like light orbs.

00:26:59.870 --> 00:27:03.300 align:middle line:84%
So I asked them to show up in
ways that we could identify

00:27:03.300 --> 00:27:06.190 align:middle line:84%
them, as in faces, as
in physical bodies,

00:27:06.190 --> 00:27:08.220 align:middle line:90%
and so on and so forth.

00:27:08.220 --> 00:27:11.290 align:middle line:84%
And interestingly enough,
when I went looking for them,

00:27:11.290 --> 00:27:14.530 align:middle line:84%
I found that I was
exhausted after going

00:27:14.530 --> 00:27:16.784 align:middle line:84%
through a garden
looking for fairies.

00:27:16.784 --> 00:27:18.700 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, I thought
that was interesting.

00:27:18.700 --> 00:27:20.570 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: And I thought
well, why is that.

00:27:20.570 --> 00:27:22.420 align:middle line:84%
It felt like I'd
installed the garden.

00:27:22.420 --> 00:27:25.620 align:middle line:84%
Because when I'd go and do
installations for people,

00:27:25.620 --> 00:27:26.490 align:middle line:90%
physically--

00:27:26.490 --> 00:27:27.490 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: A lot of work.

00:27:27.490 --> 00:27:27.990 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:27:27.990 --> 00:27:30.120 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: I was
transforming their land,

00:27:30.120 --> 00:27:34.840 align:middle line:84%
and transmuting their
whole environment

00:27:34.840 --> 00:27:37.920 align:middle line:84%
through changing
their landscape.

00:27:37.920 --> 00:27:40.510 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, I asked the
questions and what

00:27:40.510 --> 00:27:44.010 align:middle line:84%
came to me was that the nature
spirits, to show themselves

00:27:44.010 --> 00:27:49.020 align:middle line:84%
in form, have to take from our
physicality or our ectoplasm.

00:27:49.020 --> 00:27:51.960 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, wow, that
makes so much sense.

00:27:51.960 --> 00:27:54.220 align:middle line:84%
Because honestly,
I was exhausted

00:27:54.220 --> 00:27:55.304 align:middle line:90%
after going fairy hunting.

00:27:55.304 --> 00:27:56.678 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So that
they can appear

00:27:56.678 --> 00:27:59.255 align:middle line:84%
in a form that is recognizable
to you and through the camera

00:27:59.255 --> 00:27:59.420 align:middle line:90%
lens.

00:27:59.420 --> 00:28:00.045 align:middle line:90%
>>COOPER: Yeah.

00:28:00.045 --> 00:28:02.247 align:middle line:90%
Because they don't necessarily--

00:28:02.247 --> 00:28:04.455 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They have to come
from a different density.

00:28:04.455 --> 00:28:08.229 align:middle line:84%
>>COOPER: Exactly, in the same
dimensional reality that we do.

00:28:08.229 --> 00:28:09.770 align:middle line:84%
But for them to show
themselves, they

00:28:09.770 --> 00:28:12.714 align:middle line:84%
have to pull from
our physicality.

00:28:12.714 --> 00:28:14.130 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well
some of them that I

00:28:14.130 --> 00:28:17.070 align:middle line:84%
find the most beautiful
in various depictions,

00:28:17.070 --> 00:28:19.910 align:middle line:84%
including in one of the
photographs in your book,

00:28:19.910 --> 00:28:23.040 align:middle line:84%
are the undines,
the water spirits.

00:28:23.040 --> 00:28:26.000 align:middle line:84%
And when I was reading
about the water spirits

00:28:26.000 --> 00:28:29.010 align:middle line:84%
in-- I think it was this little
Fairies at Work and Play book--

00:28:29.010 --> 00:28:31.450 align:middle line:84%
